properties.areaDesc: Cape Fairweather to Cape Suckling Coastal Area
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 19 at 2:15PM AKST until February 20 at 3:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southeast winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...The Northeast Gulf Coast including Yakutat.

* WHEN...From Thursday morning through Thursday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power lines.
Widespread power outages are possible. Travel could be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Unsecured boats
could break loose.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM THURSDAY MORNING THROUGH THURSDAY AFTERNOON
